The paper deals with computational aspects of statistical relational learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study of marginal polytopes is related to machine learning and optimization, which are also covered by cs.LG and cs.DS. The paper also involves complexity-theoretic assumptions and computational problems, which are relevant to cs.CC. Finally, the use of first-order logic formulas and expected values suggests a connection to database theory and data mining, which are covered by cs.DM.
